<div class="family-uploader container">
  <h1>Family Member Uploader</h1>

  <p>A CSV or Excel file can be used to import family records. Excel formats must be XLS for versions of excel (1997-2003) or XLSX (2007 or later).</p>
  <p>Download an import template in <%= link_to "Excel Format", family_member_imports_path(format: "xls") %>. but be sure to save this file with the correct extension.</p>
  <p>If you prefer to use your own CSV file or EXCEL spreadsheet, the following column headers are required:</p>

  <ul id="import-headers">
    <li><p>first_name</p></li>
    <li><p>age</p></li>
    <li><p>gender</p></li>
    <li><p>size_pants</p></li>
    <li><p>size_shirt</p></li>
    <li><p>size_dress</p></li>
    <li><p>size_shoes</p></li>
    <li><p>bio</p></li>
    <li><p>drive_id (Drive.last.id)</p></li>
    <li><p>code</p></li>
    <li><p>name</p></li>
  </ul>

  <p> 
    In addition to these columns, you may also add optional "needs" columns as "need1", "need2", "need3", and so on. Doing so will associate desired gifts/needs with the family member upon spreadsheet import.
  </p>

  <%= form_for [@family_members] do |f| %>
  <% if @family_members.errors.any? %>
  <div id="import-errors">
    <h2><%= pluralize(@family_members.errors.count, "error") %> prohibited this import form completing:</h2>
    <ul>
      <% @family_members.errors.full_messages.each do |message| %>
      <li><%= message %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <% end %>

  <div id="import-field">
    <%= f.file_field :file, :id => "import_file" %>
    <%= f.submit "Import", :id => "import_blue_link" %>
  </div>
  <% end %>

</div>
</div>



